{"pattern": "A bottle is a container, typically made of glass, ceramic, plastic, aluminium or other impermeable material, used to hold liquids (water, milk, beer, soft drinks, wine, chemicals, medicine, etc.) and solids (food, powders, pills). Bottles are often recycled according to the SPI recycling code for the material. Some regions have a legally mandated deposit which is refunded after returning an empty bottle to the retailer. Bottles are best known for containing beverages, but are also used to store chemicals, cosmetics, medicine, food, oil, perfume, and water. Common design types include bottles, flasks, jars, and vials.
